9
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:27,130
it’s also important to praise the Party
when they do things well.

10
00:00:27,130 --> 00:00:28,650
So I will.

11
00:00:28,650 --> 00:00:32,160
The Chinese Communist Party is really, really
good...

12
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:36,730
at turning their terrible mistakes into propaganda
wins—

13
00:00:36,730 --> 00:00:39,300
and convincing the rest of the world to agree.

14
00:00:39,300 --> 00:00:42,620
They’re doing it right now with the coronavirus.

15
00:00:42,620 --> 00:00:44,630
And they’ve done it before, too.

16
00:00:44,630 --> 00:00:49,040
For example, after Mao Zedong took over in
1949

17
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:51,360
and enforced collective farming,

18
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:56,190
the Chinese Communist Party plunged the nation
into poverty and starvation.

19
00:00:56,190 --> 00:00:59,640
Then, Deng Xiaoping made free market reforms,

20
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:02,650
and Chinese people were able to make a living
again.

21
00:01:02,650 --> 00:01:05,460
But the Chinese Communist Party spun it

22
00:01:05,460 --> 00:01:08,890
as if *they* lifted people out of poverty—

23
00:01:08,890 --> 00:01:11,470
even though it was actually Chinese people
themselves

24
00:01:11,470 --> 00:01:15,440
who worked their way out of poverty once the
Party

25
00:01:15,440 --> 00:01:19,440
