policies.

26
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:23,110
Here’s how Chinese Chinese state-run media
covers it:

27
00:01:23,110 --> 00:01:26,060
China lifts millions of people out of poverty.

28
00:01:26,060 --> 00:01:28,500
The Communist Party has gotten respected

29
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:30,900
global institutions like the World Bank

30
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:33,680
to carry that same line.

31
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:37,060
Then Chinese state-run media repeat their
propaganda,

32
00:01:37,060 --> 00:01:41,210
this time citing the World Bank to make it
sound legit.

33
00:01:41,210 --> 00:01:46,030
Then Western media pick up the story because
the World Bank said it.

34
00:01:46,030 --> 00:01:50,420
So all the credit for “lifting people out
of poverty” goes to “China”—

35
00:01:50,420 --> 00:01:51,420
i.e.

36
00:01:51,420 --> 00:01:53,150
The Chinese Communist Party.

37
00:01:53,150 --> 00:01:57,560
And nowhere does that article mention how
the Chinese Communist Party

38
00:01:57,560 --> 00:02:00,510
put all those people in poverty in the first
place!

39
00:02:00,510 --> 00:02:03,670
It’s like you throw someone overboard,

40
00:02:03,670 --> 00:02:06,740
watch them struggle to swim, and then eventually

41
00:02:06,740 --> 00:02:11,319
you throw them a rope and watch them claw
their way back to the boat.

42
00:02:11,319 --> 00:02:14,500
And now you’re the hero for saving them.

43
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:19,150
The Chinese Communist Party has repeated the
same playbook over and over—

44
00:02:19,150 --> 00:02:21,100
like with faking GDP growth,

45
00:02:21,100 --> 00:02:24,790
or covering up their shady organ transplant
business,

46
00:02:24,790 --> 00:02:28,819
or hiding how they’re putting Uighurs in
concentration camps.

47
00:02:28,819 --> 00:02:32,970
